Vacation Excitement (Rephrased)

Chef is planning a vacation with his friends in March, and he is very excited about it.

The vacation will start on the X-th day of March.

Chef’s excitement level on March 1st is Y.
Every day that passes, his excitement increases by 1.

So his excitement will be:

Y on March 1

Y + 1 on March 2

Y + 2 on March 3

and it continues increasing like this every day.

Your task is to find Chef’s excitement level on the day his vacation begins.

Input

The input contains two integers separated by a space:

X – the day in March when the vacation starts

Y – Chef’s excitement level on March 1st

Output

Print a single integer representing Chef’s excitement level on the day the vacation begins.

